name: Low-Carb Pumpkin Cheesecake Bars
author: Paula Todora (Paula T)
summary: Low-carb cheesecake bars with few ingredients. They taste like the inside of a pumpkin pie!
ingredients: 1 cup granular sucralose sweetener (such as Splenda®)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Spray an 8-inch glass baking dish with cooking spray
Place cream cheese in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment; beat on high speed until smooth
Add pumpkin puree, eggs, sweetener, pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon, and vanilla extract
Pour batter into the prepared dish
Bake in the preheated oven until center is set, about 40 minutes
Cool to room temperature before serving, or serve cold
